Q3 Performance:
The third quarter of 2022 featured more macro volatility from equity selloffs and tightening monetary policy in the US to wild swings in the British pound. Through all this, fine wine markets stayed in positive territory and gained momentum as the quarter progressed.

We remain confident fine wine can continue to display stability and deliver positive returns despite the gloomy macro backdrop. However, a degree of caution is warranted in the near term and certain market segments could fair better than others.

Our Q3 performance update highlights the main trends over the quarter and delves into our outlook for the end of the year. [Read the full Q3 report]
